									</header>
									<span class="image main"><img src="images/pic11.jpg" alt="Problem Definition" /></span>
									
									<h2>Core Problem Statement</h2>
									<p>Montefiore Square currently functions as an underutilized and disconnected public space that fails to meet the needs of the surrounding Harlem community. Despite its strategic location near transit, educational institutions, and residential areas, the plaza suffers from design deficiencies that limit its potential as a vibrant community hub.</p>
									
									<hr class="major" />
									
									<h2>Key Challenges Identified</h2>
									
									<div class="row">
										<div class="col-6 col-12-small">
											<h3>1. Safety Concerns</h3>
											<ul>
												<li>Poor lighting creates unsafe conditions after dark</li>
												<li>Limited visibility across the plaza</li>
												<li>Conflicts between pedestrian and vehicle movements</li>
												<li>Lack of emergency call points or safety infrastructure</li>
											</ul>
										</div>
										<div class="col-6 col-12-small">
											<h3>2. Comfort Deficiencies</h3>
											<ul>
												<li>Insufficient shade and seating</li>
												<li>Hardscape dominance with minimal greenery</li>
												<li>No protection from sun, wind, or rain</li>
												<li>Uncomfortable surface materials</li>
											</ul>
										</div>
										<div class="col-6 col-12-small">
											<h3>3. Accessibility Barriers</h3>
											<ul>
												<li>Uneven pavement surfaces</li>
												<li>Limited ADA-compliant pathways</li>
												<li>Insufficient seating for elderly and disabled users</li>
												<li>Barriers to visibility and navigation</li>
											</ul>
										</div>
										<div class="col-6 col-12-small">
											<h3>4. Lack of Programming</h3>
											<ul>
												<li>No flexible spaces for events or markets</li>
												<li>Absence of community gathering areas</li>
												<li>Limited amenities for different user groups</li>
												<li>No integration with local business activity</li>
											</ul>
										</div>
									</div>
									
									<hr class="major" />
									
									<h2>User Impact</h2>
									<p>These deficiencies affect different user groups in distinct ways:</p>
									
									<div class="table-wrapper">
										<table>
											<thead>
												<tr>
													<th>User Group</th>
													<th>Current Experience</th>
													<th>Desired Experience</th>
												</tr>
											</thead>
											<tbody>
												<tr>
													<td>Residents</td>
													<td>No nearby gathering space; unsafe after dark</td>
													<td>Safe, comfortable neighborhood hub</td>
												</tr>
												<tr>
													<td>Students (CCNY)</td>
													<td>No outdoor study or social space</td>
													<td>Shaded seating, WiFi, charging stations</td>
												</tr>
												<tr>
													<td>Seniors</td>
													<td>Difficult to navigate; no resting places</td>
													<td>Accessible paths, frequent seating, shade</td>
												</tr>
												<tr>
													<td>Commuters</td>
													<td>Unpleasant transit waiting experience</td>
													<td>Protected waiting areas, clear wayfinding</td>
												</tr>
												<tr>
													<td>Local Businesses</td>
													<td>No connection to plaza activity</td>
													<td>Spill-out space, event opportunities</td>
												</tr>
											</tbody>
										</table>
									</div>
									
									<hr class="major" />
									
									<h2>Opportunity Statement</h2>
									<p>By addressing these interconnected challenges, the redesign of Montefiore Square presents an opportunity to:</p>
									<ul>
										<li>Create a model for community-centered public space in Harlem</li>
										<li>Demonstrate how AI-assisted design can enhance traditional urban planning</li>
										<li>Activate underutilized urban land for public benefit</li>
										<li>Support local economic activity and community cohesion</li>
										<li>Improve public health through increased physical activity and social connection</li>
									</ul>
									
